# Technical Stack
Date Last Modified: March 20, 2025

## Frontend
- Next.js 15.x for the React framework
- React 19.x for UI components
- TypeScript for type safety
- Tailwind CSS for styling with shadcn/ui component library
- React Hook Form for form handling
- Zod for schema validation
- Lucide React for icons

## Backend
- Next.js API routes for backend functionality
- Firebase for authentication, database, and storage
- Google Gemini AI for document processing and data extraction

## Data Storage
- Firebase Firestore for database
- Firebase Storage for file storage (PDFs)
- Proper data modeling with denormalization when needed
- Implement proper indexing for frequently queried fields

## Authentication
- Firebase Authentication for user management
- Implement proper role-based access control
- Secure routes with authentication middleware
- Handle authentication state properly in the frontend

## Deployment
- Vercel for hosting the Next.js application
- Docker for containerization when needed
- Implement proper CI/CD pipelines
- Use environment variables for configuration